ected runTest method that increases suiteTestCalls. But wait, am I really using an anonymous class effectively here? \\n\\nIt seems I don't need dynamic class loading, which simplifies things. I wonder how Native Image metadata handles this with anonymous classes—could there be an issue? I’ll keep this in mind as I proceed.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating testing compatibility**\\n\\nI'm noticing a potential issue with the current Gradle setup using the JUnit Jupiter engine through TCK. It seems like the testImplementation dependency might have ant-junit transitive which is likely tied to JUnit4, but there's also JUnit5 to consider. However, existing tests are compiling, so that's a good sign! I just need to make sure the necessary imports are in place to avoid any confusion. Let's clarify this setup further!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_MBSaQ5VMgfhrPUYqZGQEmCL6|fc_092ad9018afe4883016a263b59daa08190b19d6ebc799b6573", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.ant/ant-junit/1.10.15/src/test/java/org_apache_ant/ant_junit/JUnitTestRunnerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_apache_ant.ant_junit;\n\nimport junit.framework.TestCase;\nimport junit.framework.TestSuite;\n\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.optional.junit.JUnitTest;\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.optional.junit.JUnitTestRunner;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class JUnitTestRunnerTest {\n    @org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n    void runsSuiteReturnedByStaticSuiteMethod() {\n        SuiteMethodTest.reset();\n        JUnitTest junitTest = new JUnitTest(SuiteMethodTest.class.getName());\n        JUnitTestRunner runner = new JUnitTestRunner(junitTest, false, false, false);\n\n        runner.run();\n\n        assertThat(runner.getRetCode()).isEqualTo(JUnitTestRunner.SUCCESS);\n        assertThat(SuiteMethodTest.suiteCalls).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(SuiteMethodTest.executedTests).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(junitTest.runCount()).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(junitTest.failureCount()).isZero();\n        assertThat(junitTest.errorCount()).isZero();\n    }\n\n    @org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n    void skipsNonTestsScanFindsJUnit4TestMethods() {\n        DirectJUnit4Test.reset();\n        JUnitTest junitTest = new JUnitTest(DirectJUnit4Test.class.getName());\n        junitTest.setSkipNonTests(true);\n        JUnitTestRunner runner = new JUnitTestRunner(junitTest, false, false, false);\n\n        runner.run();\n\n        assertThat(runner.getRetCode()).isEqualTo(JUnitTestRunner.SUCCESS);\n        assertThat(DirectJUnit4Test.executedTests).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(junitTest.runCount()).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(junitTest.failureCount()).isZero();\n        assertThat(junitTest.errorCount()).isZero();\n    }\n\n    public static final class SuiteMethodTest {\n        private static int suiteCalls;\n        private static int executedTests;\n\n        public static void reset() {\n            suiteCalls = 0;\n            executedTests = 0;\n        }\n\n        public static junit.framework.Test suite() {\n            suiteCalls++;\n            TestSuite suite = new TestSuite(SuiteMethodTest.class.getName());\n            suite.addTest(new SuiteMethodTestCase());\n            return suite;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class SuiteMethodTestCase extends TestCase {\n        @Override\n        protected void runTest() {\n            SuiteMethodTest.executedTests++;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class DirectJUnit4Test {\n        private static int executedTests;\n\n        public static void reset() {\n            executedTests = 0;\n        }\n\n        @org.junit.Test\n        public void executesAsJUnit4Test() {\n            executedTests++;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1219, "output": 1977, "cacheRead": 23552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26748, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780890432830, "responseId": "resp_092ad9018afe4883016a263b416258819089bef7e82ceb873d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_MBSaQ5VMgfhrPUYqZGQEmCL6|fc_092ad9018afe4883016a263b59daa08190b19d6ebc799b6573", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 2829 bytes to tests/src/org.apache.ant/ant-junit/1.10.15/src/test/java/org_apache_ant/ant_junit/JUnitTestRunnerTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780890463335}]}
