ut how JUnit scans compiled classes and implements platform discovery. It seems like it might include patterns like *Tests? The test configuration might set this up. I'm curious about how specific these patterns need to be. Do they rely on naming conventions? I want to ensure I'm considering all possible implications for how tests are recognized within the framework. Understanding this could help clarify how to organize my tests effectively.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_092ad9018afe4883016a263b6df9588190876d02b32d87b423\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJjt-l0R2iIREsIAbDsUUCI-gNJK-pmzF-J6QJ4DNfVSkzMtmEgruf00lDt1_phlJNtC7zsSsJzu2ZB7OwBfYxJpECBUg65TOdQbZcKf_jzsCtDP0o1YSuq9TKNQ7GBmLvGrJIIus5Np1ts3lvWaNBxJnHgoht58WyWZlDJkfctyegjRDQk7jTZ0vhXE-F5vmVUuiw6OBAvSXwNpAbIxbCUteszbibv1pK6fsQZdQk8Wizuz4SzTAG7dhm08iPqPMH6Qnuoutb6EpmTyw4rJAXjdh3NpUwvqdnB4d8nLtyAgKp2Sgg9kW8v3GqilX78VKrPIx1AGD7vKFTFIdXNL0EVtr3ddTgi34Slbv9OFvS5oHnEnMmnn3zmt6yrthhEyYX5MHejKCE5fhrdbolG_Q9jN-4nEOhxgNfey3n6T9p3hbqFIAXsoTzWSFpueSywEMKBvDJ-VrMn-fT28BQEYOOU57UwSDBvnM0feVcDLMmL2qK9vlvbsOKVIq9c-5uA_XsyzYc-mwEN2AfwsWJ8--jltyYrBKBxXeaP4yx1JsXvdUVITQKGtoyWVqlrOi1Yy0yo3je1oDo32LeaKi8Ov2h_ANWL1UdlU0bHb0uHt6o4maS_kUM7ODNGnV_i9yXgxqRuOQnsqbw7i_wZEIFV1wru7qmAmdcZLEsKwW3Sdfru1n9gwY9SVkopwHlgKDhCMcp_P-P-R_tyLGrmjqAZj4YWf2a_d1RQ0KX6A-0Z1VU_vOinIj4LLqiuBlqG6QjLXlok35OGN9GFz89J6ZTJRdHK4nojjcPEflCC2InyOlOcMSwNQBhWflbNFiWT0palX5ASYwtVmkT4439oGrYFOOihfh1dPtDjF2h_-z_6V5QX8vkCIyvAcxmkqEwRIr2OcCT739QlMx7cXoxh6wqUX99mvdYTUXH92mU2RO0KowRRHStQDrtIZkNDrxN-rVmiQoKVno_IPrVdAloVj2ieuhoQcHAUf_zaGkQoYwAV5daxqvKbDcleEBtyvb03w0WjNevu7neLOBodeWyb0vOqCRwGbJBLM9Eet4mlj4X4jPv---D5vQDbOiQ1Gl-c30JD-Z9aJ0FIk7fg7sIpZFMCUvF-J_R2qRlFo23YqKpp3bMYd6xVdbxPqPYgOmfTipnFq8XCK-BZtzfyy0j9ihW0o83X0H9xJ3jOwiQdn79tNDFlwK15frfK0gFO5-dbAr_MzZ7DTsOO2TKtM33KJVaYCxAiKE37d3YrjeP2AcaelmYQl4Z41_-AtyJdJAKhI9g4kGXHW3g21zZwz2te2fYT9iUa_4AKYQZ1t4yL-UEbIyMN0qL-9rcWDWlnYLIi-KnwSPgMnzJut2X9-N7kUKXiFC6ZuCs30VFQVPOdgTOdEDUgaP87giyA