tion. I consider the need for a public static suite method that returns junit.framework.Test. I might inspect Gradle dependencies and see if existing configurations support excluding certain patterns. Should I check if exclusion rules are too restrictive? I’ll want to avoid skipping important tests.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining native image and test classes**\\n\\nI'm considering whether native image includes test classes, even if they're excluded from JUnit execution. They would still compile and be available in the classpath. I think users might need the TCK Gradle plugin for native image builds. Excluding classes from test discovery should fix JVM issues, but native images may still include these classes. I wonder if using an exclude pattern like \\\"**/*Fixture.class\\\" will work effectively. It might be best to avoid altering the build config, but I'll also consider annotating fixtures. Let's edit the build.gradle for exclusions carefully.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Rethinking the suite method**\\n\\nI'm considering whether to simplify the suite method by adding varargs. I wonder if JUnitTestRunner.getMethod(\\\"suite\\\") is not finding it. It seems necessary to ensure line coverage as getMethod tries and catches exceptions, which should cover cases where the suite method is absent. The invoke method needs to confirm that the suiteMethod isn't null. I also think about using `@org.junit.platform.commons.annotation.Testable`, but I'm unsure if that's applicable. It looks like the suite method remains essential.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JCy0VkSf4vdFBvFCPnLCGhCQ|fc_092ad9018afe4883016a263bedd7288190852637faefdedb8f", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.ant/ant-junit/1.10.15/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "dependencies {\n    testImplementation \"org.apache.ant:ant-junit:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n}\n\ngraalvmNative {", "newText": "dependencies {\n    testImplementation \"org.apache.ant:ant-junit:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n}\n\ntasks.withType(Test).configureEach {\n    exclude '**/JUnitTestRunnerTest$*.class'\n}\n\ngraalvmNative {"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5365, "output": 1925, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36474, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780890569330, "responseId": "resp_092ad9018afe4883016a263bca4c50819097e0f26bceba10ec"}}
