[thinking] **Considering JUnit testing**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about helper classes versus top-level tests. I realize that JUnit Platform discovers classes, even helper ones. Using @Ignore to hide a fixture might be okay since it skips its discovery as a test. I'm wondering if we can avoid using @Ignore for the actual `JUnit3Fixture`. Since it gets recognized as a test, I’m considering alternatives, like using build config exclusions, but I feel that might not be the right direction either.
[thinking] 
